privacy /ˈpraɪvəsɪ/

1. N-UNCOUNT If you have privacy , you are in a place or situation that allows you to do things without other people seeing you or disturbing you. 隐私; 私人空间 

例： He resented the publication of this book, which he saw as an embarrassing invasion of his privacy. 他憎恨这本书的出版，它将此看作是对其隐私的令人难堪的侵犯。 

例： Thatched pavilions provide shady retreats for relaxing and reading in privacy. 茅亭为独自放松和看书提供阴凉的幽僻之所。

